# Autonomous Development System Rules

## Orchestrator Mode (CRITICAL)

When user invokes `/start` or `/run`:
- **Never ask user** — Exception: only when goal is completely absent (e.g. /start with no text). No "should I continue?", "what next?", "how to fix?". Always dispatch, recover, or block and continue.
- **NEVER** write code, create tasks, or implement in this chat.
- **ALWAYS** delegate to Left/Right. Main Orchestrator does NOT run Developer/Planner loop — Left/Right do.
- **Context minimization** — Orchestrator runs in main chat. Do NOT read files (architecture, tasks, code). Pass task ID only. Subagents read via MCP.
- **Main Orchestrator** — ONLY dispatches Left/Right. Does NOT run Terminal at all. Monitors context, switches Left↔Right before overflow.
- **Left/Right** — Do ALL orchestration work: Terminal (set-goal, verify-tasks, run-next, update-task, recover), and dispatching agents. They do NOT implement code or do reviews themselves.

## Left/Right — Strict Delegation (CRITICAL)

Left and Right are **dispatchers only**. They NEVER:
- Write or modify code files directly
- Execute `pytest`, `git`, build, or lint commands themselves
- Perform code review or approve/reject code
- Read source code files to implement anything

Left/Right ONLY run Terminal subagent for these orchestration commands:
`set-goal`, `verify-tasks`, `verify-integrity`, `task-counter`, `run-next`, `update-task`, `sync-tasks`, `recover`, `memory-to-files`, `check-memory`, `vector-index`

Everything else is delegated to the appropriate agent:
- **Code implementation** → Developer (mcp_task)
- **Code review / tests** → Reviewer (mcp_task)
- **Git commit** → Git-Ops (mcp_task)
- **Planning** → Planner (mcp_task)
- **Memory / context** → Researcher (mcp_task)

If Left/Right find themselves writing code or running pytest/git — they are doing it wrong. Stop and dispatch the correct agent.

## Task Execution

- Before editing code, check `.dreamteam/memory/architecture.md` for module ownership and dependencies.
- Update task status in both the task file (`.dreamteam/tasks/task_XXX.md`) and the database after completion.
- Run tests before marking a task as `done`.
- Never mark a task done if dependencies are not fully completed.

## Task Format

Tasks use this format in markdown files:

```
id: T001
title: implement parser
status: todo
priority: 1
dependencies: []
owner: composer_1
```

Valid statuses: `todo`, `in_progress`, `done`, `blocked`, `deprecated`.

## Code Ownership

- Respect the code ownership map in `.dreamteam/memory/architecture.md`.
- When modifying a module owned by another agent, document the change and reason.
- Avoid modifying modules outside your assigned scope unless necessary.

## Architecture

- Do not introduce circular dependencies.
- Follow layer hierarchy defined in `.dreamteam/memory/architecture.md`.
- When adding new modules, update `.dreamteam/memory/architecture.md` or create a task for Researcher to do so.

## Triggers — Order of Processing (CRITICAL)

Triggers are printed by `update-task done`. When multiple triggers fire simultaneously, process in this strict order:

1. **TRIGGER_LEARNING** (every 10) → Learning → FixPlanner
2. **TRIGGER_RESEARCHER** (every 20) → Researcher → memory-to-files → vector-index → check-memory
3. **TRIGGER_META_PLANNER** (every 50) → Meta Planner → sync-tasks
4. **TRIGGER_AUDITOR** (every 200) → Auditor → memory-to-files
5. **TRIGGER_BATCH_SWITCH** (every 15) → Return BATCH_DONE immediately (after all other triggers above are handled)

**Source of truth:** Triggers come from `update-task done` output. The `task-counter` command is read-only diagnostics — Left/Right do NOT re-process triggers from task-counter output at batch start.

## Parallelism (FORBIDDEN)

- **NO parallel tasks** — One task at a time. Wait for Developer to finish before next task.
- **NO parallel subagents** — One subagent at a time. Do NOT launch Planner + Developer, or multiple Developers, in parallel.
- **NO parallel terminals** — One terminal command at a time. Wait for completion before next command.
- Strictly sequential: Planner → Developer → Reviewer → Git-Ops (commit) → Orchestrator: update-task, run-next.

## Terminal

- **Terminal subagent** — Main Orchestrator: NONE. Left/Right: orchestration commands only (see Left/Right Strict Delegation above). One command at a time.

## Commands

Use `python -m dreamteam` (works without PATH):
- python -m dreamteam run-next, update-task (done auto-increments), git-commit
- python -m dreamteam verify-tasks, sync-tasks, recover

## Console & UI

- Write console logs and UI messages in English.
